    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-07-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-07-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="458"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d458">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Hale.</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 73.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-07-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 23, 1867.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your despatches to No. 95,
                    inclusive. Herewith I enclose for your further information a transcript of a
                        note<note n="*" xml:id="d458fn1">For inclosure see despatch No. 39, June
                        18th, from United States Minister to Ecuador.</note> which was addressed to
                    the minister resident of the United States at Quito, by the minister for foreign
                    affairs of the republic of Ecuador, on the 17th of June last, on the subject of
                    the proposition by this government to mediate by the use of its good offices for
                    the restoration of peace between Spain and the allied republics of South
                    America.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John P. Hale</hi>, Esq.,<hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
